                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>WELCOME TO THIS SELF-REFLECTION</h4><div><p><b>Exploring My Own Biases</b></p><p>This short reflection exercise is designed to help you explore your own patterns of thinking and behaviour. There are no right or wrong answers â€“ this is simply an opportunity for honest self-reflection.</p><p>Taking a few minutes to consider how you typically think and react will help you get more out of the upcoming live session.</p></div></div></div>

<div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="privacy-notice"><h4><span>ðŸ”’</span> IMPORTANT: THIS IS A PRIVATE REFLECTION</h4><ul><li><b>Your responses are completely private</b> â€“ they are not saved, submitted, or shared with anyone</li><li><b>This is not assessed</b> â€“ there is no score and no "correct" answers</li><li><b>Be honest with yourself</b> â€“ the value of this exercise comes from genuine self-reflection</li><li><b>Purpose:</b> To bring personal awareness into the live session, helping you engage more meaningfully with the content</li></ul></div></div>

<div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>How this works:</b></p><p>You will be presented with 8 reflective statements about everyday thoughts and behaviours. For each statement, simply indicate whether you:</p><ul><li><b>Agree</b> â€“ This sounds like me</li><li><b>Unsure</b> â€“ I am not certain, or it depends on the situation</li><li><b>Disagree</b> â€“ This does not sound like me</li></ul><p>After completing the statements, you will have the opportunity to note any insights or patterns you have noticed.</p><p><b>Time required:</b> 5-10 minutes</p></div></div></div>
